article.headline: Jacksonville University 76, Kennesaw State 72
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Ben Smith scored a career-high 20 points as Jacksonville University came back from a 13-point halftime deficit to beat Kennesaw State 76-72 on Saturday night. Down 41-28 at the half, JU (13-11, 9-5 Atlantic Sun) opened the second half with a 15-5 run to cut the Owls lead to five with 15:31 left in the game. The Dolphins took their first lead since the 5:42 mark of the first half when Smith made a driving lay-up and converted the foul shot with 5:49 left in the game. Kennesaw State (11-16, 7-8) retied the game less than a minute later, but Smith converted a four-point play, making a free throw after connecting on a 3-pointer to help JU lead 56-61. The Dolphins would not trail again. Kimbrough added 19 points and had five assists. Kennesaw State had five players score in double figures led by Ragsdale's team-high 17 points, but Ragsdale fouled out when he fouled Smith. Shuan Stegall had 16 points and eight rebounds for the Owls while Andre Morgan, Jon-Michael Nickerson and Ingle had 12 each.
